WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.120
Hello, my name is Tom Wilson and I'm a former University of Arizona professor and I'm now

00:05.120 --> 00:11.440
working for SciTech Institute and we promote STEM education for all grade levels and I've

00:11.440 --> 00:16.560
been privileged enough to be able to participate in this year's event for the space settlement

00:16.560 --> 00:23.280
design competition and I it's my first time doing it I spent a lot of time here at Biosphere 2 in

00:23.280 --> 00:29.680
various capacities leading student trips and so forth but being playing this role and watching

00:29.680 --> 00:35.760
these students most of whom I've met have never participated in an event like this before getting

00:35.760 --> 00:42.960
them out of the classrooms working with strangers kids their age to put something together was for

00:42.960 --> 00:48.720
me something that it's a life-changing experience for them and one of the things over the course of

00:48.720 --> 00:55.680
the past few days that I've really been impressed by is the evolution process not just in terms of

00:55.680 --> 01:00.880
the students with their challenges or their projects taking shape over time but the individuals

01:00.880 --> 01:06.080
themselves you have introverted students coming in here and they don't know how to articulate they

01:06.080 --> 01:11.520
can't share their ideas in a way that is effective and over the course of the past several days

01:11.520 --> 01:17.280
I've seen them gel and coalesce and then you also have you know 20 plus students coming together

01:17.280 --> 01:22.000
and you know most of them are strangers to each other and bonding forming a team

01:22.960 --> 01:28.480
not only that but being able to take some incredibly technical information involving some cutting-edge

01:28.480 --> 01:34.720
science and actually doing the detective work behind it that actually shows that they can talk

01:34.720 --> 01:39.600
the talk but they can also walk the walk and back up what they're saying with some technical

01:39.600 --> 01:45.600
information it just blew me away I could never do stuff like that at their age unless I had an

01:45.680 --> 01:53.360
opportunity like this and so I think this event should be held just open it up in scope have

01:53.360 --> 01:58.720
different venues different times of the year have more participants in this because you will change

01:58.720 --> 02:05.440
people's lives and arguably that high school level age is going to be a most pivotal age for these

02:05.440 --> 02:11.360
students and it can change the course of their academic careers their professional careers and

02:11.360 --> 02:22.960
their personal development so thank you

